10/04/2003
BUCHAREST, Romania -- The foreign ministry issued a press release Wednesday (9 April), welcoming the establishment of the Balkan Trust for Democracy (BTD). 
It grew out of partnerships among the German Marshall Fund, USAID and the Charles Mott Foundation. 
The BTD will allocate a total of $25m to Albania, Bosnia and Herzegovina, Bulgaria, Croatia, Macedonia, Romania and Serbia-Montenegro, expanding the investment potential of the region. 
(Rompres - 10/04/03)
